Acer, E Ink Holdings, Wistron, TSMC, UMC: Taiwan Stocks Preview

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-04-06T00:41:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-06/acer-e-ink-holdings-wistron-tsmc-umc-taiwan-stocks-preview.html
Stocks of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  The Taiex Index rose 21.83, or 0.3 percent, to 8,705.13.  Chipmakers: Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Co. (2330
TT) and  United Microelectronics Corp. (2303)  (2303 TT) have received
increased orders after the earthquake in  Japan  disrupted
production in the nation, the Commercial Times reported, without
saying where it got the information. TSMC advanced 0.1 percent
to NT$70.70. UMC dropped 1 percent to NT$15.15.  Acer Inc. (2353)  (2353 TT): The world’s second-largest maker of
personal computers was lowered to “hold” at Deutsche Bank AG.
The 12-month share-price estimate is NT$58. The stock lost 4.8
percent to NT$57.10.  E Ink Holdings Inc. (8069)  (8069 TT): The supplier of Amazon.com
Inc.’s Kindle expects shipments of its electronic paper to
triple this year on rising demand for electronic book readers,
the Economic Daily News reported today, citing an interview with
Chairman Scott Lin. The stock gained 1.6 percent to NT$48.30.  Wistron Corp. (3231)  (3231 TT): The Taiwanese maker of  laptop
computers  for Acer Inc. will extend the deadline of a planned
stock sale after losing almost a quarter of its market value
since announcing the fund-raising. The stock increased 0.9
percent to NT$47.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Weiyi Lim in Singapore at 
 wlim26@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net . 